title: Propulsion Assignment
description: This assignment involves calculating the thrust produced by different types of rocket engines. Students will analyze various propulsion systems, compare their efficiencies, and provide a detailed report on their findings.

title: Combustion Analysis
description: In this assignment, students will study the combustion processes in rocket engines. They will analyze the fuel-to-oxidizer ratios, combustion chamber pressures, and temperatures, and produce a detailed analysis of the combustion efficiency.

title: Nozzle Design Project
description: This project requires students to design a rocket nozzle. They will need to consider factors such as nozzle shape, expansion ratios, and material selection. The final design should optimize performance while maintaining structural integrity.

title: Aerodynamics Quiz
description: This quiz will test your understanding of basic aerodynamic principles, including lift, drag, and the behavior of airflow over different surfaces. Ensure you review the key concepts from the course before attempting this quiz.

title: Flow Analysis
description: In this assignment, students will conduct a detailed flow analysis over an airfoil. You will be required to use computational fluid dynamics (CFD) tools to visualize and interpret the flow patterns, pressure distributions, and identify areas of potential improvement.

title: Heating Analysis
description: This assignment focuses on the thermal analysis of aerodynamic heating. Students will study the effects of high-speed airflow on surface temperatures and analyze the thermal protection systems used to safeguard structures from excessive heating.

title: Structural Design Task
description: In this assignment, students will be tasked with designing the structural framework of a spacecraft. This involves selecting appropriate materials, performing stress and load analysis, and ensuring the design meets the required safety and performance standards. A detailed report of your design process and findings will be submitted.

title: Orbital Calculations
description: This assignment focuses on performing orbital calculations for a satellite. Students will calculate parameters such as orbital period, velocity, and position over time. You will also analyze the effects of perturbations and plan a maneuver to adjust the satellite's orbit. A comprehensive calculation and analysis report will be required.

title: Systems Engineering Exam
description: The Systems Engineering Exam will test your understanding of spacecraft systems integration, subsystem interactions, and overall mission planning. Topics include power systems, thermal control, communication, and propulsion. Prepare to demonstrate your knowledge through a series of theoretical and practical questions.

title: Hydrocarbons
description: In this assignment, students will explore the structure, properties, and reactions of hydrocarbons. You will classify different types of hydrocarbons, analyze their physical and chemical properties, and investigate their uses in various industrial applications. A detailed report with diagrams and reaction mechanisms is required.

title: Functional Groups
description: This assignment focuses on identifying and understanding various functional groups in organic chemistry. Students will learn about the structure, properties, and reactivity of functional groups such as alcohols, ethers, aldehydes, ketones, carboxylic acids, and amines. You will provide examples of compounds containing these groups and describe their chemical behavior.

title: Stereochemistry
description: In this assignment, students will delve into the concepts of stereochemistry, including chirality, enantiomers, diastereomers, and optical activity. You will analyze the three-dimensional arrangements of atoms in molecules, predict the outcomes of stereochemical reactions, and discuss the importance of stereochemistry in biological systems and pharmaceuticals.
